text: Ho Lien Siew (5 September 1932 - 3 April 2021) was a Singaporean basketball player. He competed in the men's tournament at the 1956 Summer Olympics. He also represented the country at the 1962 Asian Games. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Singapore Category:Basketball players
